article.headline: Utah St. 57, San Jose St. 56
article.story: SAN JOSE, Calif. (AP) -- Jaycee Carroll had 22 points and seven rebounds, and Utah State barely held off San Jose State's late rally for its fifth straight victory, 57-56 on Saturday. Chaz Spicer had 16 points for the Aggies (15-5, 4-2 WAC), who thought they had broken free from the Spartans with an 11-1 run beginning with Carroll's tiebreaking 3-pointer with 15 minutes to play. Menelik Barbary had 16 points and Jamon Hill added 13 for San Jose State (2-15, 1-4), which came close to another big upset after last week's win over Fresno State. The Spartans had two last-second chances to take the lead after finishing the game with a 13-4 run. San Jose State pulled within one point on Barbary's dunk with 1:12 to play. Spicer mishandled Carroll's pass on Utah State's next possession -- but San Jose State's Julian Richardson, who got away with an apparent half-court violation moments earlier, was called for traveling under the basket with 6.3 seconds left. Spicer then missed a free throw, but leading scorer Carlton Spencer's long 3-pointer at the buzzer bounced off the backboard and out. Spencer finished with 12 points. The Aggies haven't lost to San Jose State in four meetings since 1996. Utah State also snapped a four-game road losing streak before next Saturday's visit to No. 15 Nevada.
